feet is smooth marble, untouched by time, yet faint impressions of
footsteps drift across its surface, appearing and fading without pattern.
The world behind you feels distant, as though you have stepped outside
the natural flow of fate. Ahead, the mist parts just enough to reveal 
a quiet hall waiting beyond.
