Hall of Echoed Steps~
The hall stretches forward in muted stillness, yet each step you take
is answered by anotherslightly delayed, slightly wrong. The sound does
not belong to you.
Tall mirrors line the walls, their surfaces cracked and clouded. Within
them, reflections shift independently, showing fragments of lives not
livedvictories never claimed, defeats never suffered. The air feels 
heavy with possibilities that never came to pass.
